Who We Are: 
Twitter is committed to serving the public conversation by helping users stay informed, inform others, and discuss what matters. 
Twitter is looking for Senior Product Designers to join the Platform Experience team responsible for designing and building the internal Twitter Management Console used by thousands of employees every day. In this role, you‚Äôll work with product managers, engineers, and other designers to create consistently excellent experiences which enable our teams to develop seamlessly on the Twitter platform. 
Our platform serves thousands of internal customers running the thousands of services that make up our product. You‚Äôll partner directly with internal customers on many kinds of projects and technologies that keep Twitter performing reliably and enabling new experiences. 
The Twitter Design family envisions the products that fuel Twitter‚Äôs mission to give everyone the power to create and share ideas and information instantly, without barriers. We have a direct impact on product strategy, roadmaps, and the detailed design of new experiences. We believe in building strong relationships, surpassing expectations, and having fun along the way. 
 
 Job Description 
What You'll Do 
As a member of our growing team you'll design tools that will serve internal teams at Twitter, partnering closely with Twitter engineering and Product teams to build systems at scale. This work includes our internal hybrid cloud management experience paralleling those of cloud offerings such as AWS and GCP. Your work will make it drastically easier to be a developer at Twitter, enabling Twitter to deliver for our users at increased pace. 
As a member of our growing team, you‚Äôll bring a mix of strong product design experience, ‚ÄúDesign-Thinking‚Äù methodologies, design-system knowledge, talent, expertise, and innovative product insights to the role. You‚Äôll balance a rigorous user-centric perspective with the ability to make bold decisions and move the product forward in a fast-paced development environment. You‚Äôll foster collaboration and consistency across teams and products by working closely with product managers and engineers (local & distributed) to build great experiences for developers using Twitter‚Äôs data products. You‚Äôll partner with our Research team to find opportunities and integrate user insights into product strategy and design. You will always champion user experience, product consistency, and design excellence. 
 
 Qualifications 
Who You Are 
If this sounds like a fit for you, you probably have: 
5+ years experience designing and building products for desktop experiences in a fast-paced and dynamic cross-functional environment (B2B & B2C). 
Expert in product design, user interface, interaction, visual and motion design, storytelling, and prototyping across web and mobile web platforms. 
Experience working with and contributing to design systems and componentization 
Demonstrate ability to tackle complex problems and be able to identify and mitigate risks. 
Excellent communication, presentation and collaboration skills with a strong ability to influence cross-functionally at all levels. 
Experience being a design lead who leads large projects and direct/mentor other designers. 
Passion for identifying and solving customer problems. 
Comfort in a fast-paced, highly-dynamic environment with multiple stakeholders. 
Skilled with Figma (or Sketch) and prototyping tools such as Framer, Principle. 
Comfortable presenting and working with senior executives 
Embraces and encourages diverse perspectives to inspire product thinking. 
Business acumen. 
#LoveTwitter 
Added bonus 
Great but not required: 
Experience building complex internal-tools. 
Experience with machine learning and artificial intelligence 
A passion for and interest in data and data visualization. 
Some experience with basic coding (HTML, CSS, Javascript or other). 
